oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Ralph Boston in his 1968 U. S. Olympic Team Track Uniform
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Tennessee State University
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Ralph Boston, a 1961 Graduate of Tennessee A & I State University (Now Tennessee State University), Is Pictured in His United States Olympic Track Uniform With His Running Shoes. He Specialized in the Long Jump and Won a Gold Medal at the 1960 Rome Olympics, a Silver Medal at the 1964 Toyko Olympics and a Bronze Medal at the 1968 Mexico City Olympics.
